identity: |
  Replace this with a multi-line description of who you are, what you work on,
  and what you care about. The scoring step uses this verbatim, so be honest
  and specific. A few paragraphs is fine.

themes:
  tech:
    weight: high
    description: |
      What within tech do you actually want to read about. Be specific —
      "AI agents and applied ML" beats "AI in general".
  thinking:
    weight: high
    description: |
      Epistemics, decision-making, philosophy, learning, expertise.
  business:
    weight: medium
    description: |
      Startups, strategy, economics, markets, management.
  science:
    weight: medium
    description: |
      Physics, biology, neuroscience, research methodology, mathematics.
  culture:
    weight: low
    description: |
      Books, films, history, broader cultural ideas.

avoid:
  - hype-driven crypto content
  - low-substance reaction videos
  - listicles and engagement-bait

style_preferences: |
  Prefer depth over brevity. Skip filler. If something doesn't have a real
  argument behind it, score it low.
